# CODEOWNERS — changes to matched paths require review from the listed owners.
# https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositories-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
#
# Enforcement requires "Require review from Code Owners" branch protection on
# `master` (tracked in #4772). NOTE: GitHub requires at least ONE listed code
# owner to approve a matched change — it cannot natively require that BOTH
# owners below approve. To approximate that, also set required approvals to 2.

# The npm publishing workflow is the supply-chain security perimeter: with
# trusted publishing, whoever can change this file can change what gets
# published and how. Guard it tightly.
#
# NOTE: this guards *changes to* the workflow files. It does NOT restrict who
# can trigger publish_to_npm.yml via workflow_dispatch — anyone with repo write
# access can. That path is mitigated separately: a dispatched `release` runs
# `npm stage publish`, which still requires a maintainer's 2FA staging approval
# before anything goes live. Restricting workflow_dispatch is a GitHub setting,
# not expressible here.
/.github/workflows/   @michaelbromley @dlhck

# Protect this file itself, so the ownership rules can't be removed without
# the same owners signing off.
/.github/CODEOWNERS    @michaelbromley @dlhck
